com.incadencecorp.coalesce.services.common

Class ServiceBase<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.incadencecorp.coalesce.services.common.ServiceBase<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICoalesceExecutorService, AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CrudServiceImpl, SearchServiceImpl

    public abstract class ServiceBase<T>
extends Object
implements ICoalesceExecutorService, AutoCloseable
    Base class for handling the queuing of jobs asynchronously, returning the results, and the collection of metrics. Must call dispose to free up resources.
    Author:
    Derek C.

      • cancelJob

        public final StringResponse cancelJob(JobRequest request)
        Cancels a submitted job. Canceling a job will remove it from the queue, therefore status for this job will no longer be provided.
        Parameters:
        request - the request
        Returns:
        BaseResponse.getStatus() which states if cancel was successful.

      • performJob

        public final <REQUEST extends BaseRequest,RESPONSE extends ICoalesceResponseType<List<X>>,X extends ICoalesceResponseType<?>> RESPONSE performJob(AbstractServiceJob<REQUEST,RESPONSE,X,T> job)
        Runs a job. If AbstractServiceJob.isAsync() is true then its queued within the thread pool and the requester should use pickupJobResults(com.incadencecorp.coalesce.services.api.common.JobRequest) to pick up the response.
        Parameters:
        job - AbstractServiceJob
        Returns:
        the response with results if AbstractServiceJob.isAsync() is false; Otherwise a response with no results and a AbstractCoalesceJob.getJobId() that can be used to request the results once the job has completed.
